div.p:
Areas of priority attention would be taxation; exploitation of farmers,
                    fishermen, and small artisans by middlemen; inefficient government procedures;
                    use of foreign aid; joint U.S.-RVN budgeting;
                    and marketing policies for rice, fish, and fertilizer.

Item B 1—Prospects and measures proposed by Country Team
for improved prosecution of the war under the new government (Political,
including possibility of improved relations with neighboring States)
